  "prompt": "What is the best way to get change for the new 2000 INR note?",
  "response": "To get change for the new 2000 INR note, you can consider the following options:\n\n1. **Local Shops and Businesses**: Small retailers, grocery stores, or local markets often have the ability to break larger notes. Purchasing a small item can help you get change.\n\n2. **ATMs**: Use an ATM that dispenses smaller denominations. Withdrawals from ATMs will typically provide you with various smaller note denominations, which can help you break the larger 2000 INR note.\n\n3. **Banks**: Visit a nearby bank branch. Banks will usually provide change for larger denominations, especially for new currency notes.\n\n4. **Friends and Family**: Ask friends or family members if they can give you change for the 2000 INR note.\n\n5. **Public Transport**: Some public transport services (like buses or taxis) may be able to provide change if you purchase a ticket.\n\n6. **Restaurants and Cafes**: Dining at a restaurant or cafe can also provide you with the opportunity to get change when paying the bill.\n\n7. **Petty Cash at Work**: If you have access to an office or workplace with petty cash, you might be able to get change from there.\n\nBe mindful to check if the business you are trying to get change from accepts new currency notes, as there may still be some places that try to avoid them.",
